<paragraph id="C2839A137407834BB53E948249A88553" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<emphasis id="E70595EBA51D15DB14F2072A5396CCF0" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
(Fig. 
<figureCitation id="9519FC50E74C3527798661B0A5787C1A" captionStart="Figure 46" captionStartId="F46" captionText="Figure 46. Distribution of S. multiflorum." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.198.79514.figure46" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/689739" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">46</figureCitation>
).
</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="32B341626AB5A70F44EE1FCAE6137D35" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Solanum multiflorum" order="Solanales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="multiflorum">
<emphasis id="D9191D09CC2C710F752CA8D2313191DD" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Solanum multiflorum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is endemic to the western part of Tamil Nadu Province in southern India, occurring in the Nilgiri, Coimbatore, Didingul and Madurai districts.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="7A0940A260F369C3442F5F697BE9DF1C" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="ecology">
<paragraph id="9A8789593FBB38A344AC868C4B2C91D4" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Ecology and habitat.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A63295AB391DEF115BD6899CBBAD1B69" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<taxonomicName id="0B9E49D183A1CBCF3A9E195CDFD30817" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Solanum multiflorum" order="Solanales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="multiflorum">
<emphasis id="02C7A67C17C54F819ACC34B211D3BBA9" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Solanum multiflorum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a plant of deciduous or evergreen broadleaf forests and grows in forest edges and roadsides; from 1,700 to 2,300 m elevation.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="6E9B89FB758990E452D98DC877C4427E" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="common names and uses">
<paragraph id="BCDCBDA44DDDC10DDBF69DDF42E6A697" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Common names and uses.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="F04B398720738D31E4F6CACD7144D674" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
India. Karnataka: kahi sunde (
<emphasis id="E5F386A903DC8ECFDEB00F7A2040032A" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Hosagoudar 96871</emphasis>
); Tamil Nadu: 
<normalizedToken id="DDDF91CD97EC8005EB0BD89A539D14FC" originalValue="soumbé">soumbe</normalizedToken>
(
<emphasis id="92BB434B5FBBF0EA88DB1C3728436C7A" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Leschenault de la Tour 163</emphasis>
). Some of the names attributed to 
<taxonomicName id="2141CFCF80A75A0A7DCBDBF24AE98C2B" family="Solanaceae" genus="S." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="S. indicum" order="Solanales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="indicum">
<emphasis id="6004B885AD89B7AC85696CA9738E716F" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">S. indicum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in floras may refer to this species.
</paragraph>
<caption id="3B5F5B4602CA7179A5F3CA824E5A3F4A" doi="10.3897/phytokeys.198.79514.figure46" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/689739" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" start="Figure 46" startId="F46">
<paragraph id="0D8EEEAF014A04EA067B137DC3D90963" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<emphasis id="593C25924201E6BE08E6EF1D3E37B97A" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Figure 46.</emphasis>
Distribution of 
<taxonomicName id="CC22CD9FC21610DE8E9AB4C2819EDF04" family="Solanaceae" genus="S." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="S. multiflorum" order="Solanales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="multiflorum">
<emphasis id="3BCD86A3A929C093FDF5217A9CBF0677" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">S. multiflorum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</caption>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="FA410384C4D02EB775DFE64CCFA3B5E0" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="preliminary conservation status">
<paragraph id="BD953E88B9BA8B366FB53F15CBA9B196" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Preliminary conservation status</paragraph>
<paragraph id="072BA88E4A52A0C60B60D8BA1C07C153" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<emphasis id="F443FDA756D56DD555AE3A767BCC5791" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
(
<bibRefCitation id="A87A194901516E82F5174C17EBB91984" author="Hutchings, A" journalOrPublisher="AGRIVITA Journal of Agricultural Science" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" publicationUrl="http://www.iucnredlist.org/documents/RedListGuidelines.pdf" refId="B105" refString="2019. . http://www.iucnredlist.org/documents/RedListGuidelines.pdf" url="http://www.iucnredlist.org/documents/RedListGuidelines.pdf" year="2019">IUCN 2019</bibRefCitation>
).
</emphasis>
Least Concern (LC). EOO (669,122 km2, LC); AOO (324 km2, EN). 
<taxonomicName id="399B0CA7000589F71BB4798167CC8D76" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Solanum multiflorum" order="Solanales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="multiflorum">
<emphasis id="50DD89C0466928FA35DDD5D843E526F3" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Solanum multiflorum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a species of disturbed habitats in southern India, with many recent collections. It is not of particular conservation concern.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="F914DB372B3F6B4F93D8EAC61E82FC69" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="EA2AAAE0BAD5716838281C94F849EEB8" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Discussion.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB8B6FC9D7DB89BA351B14C8DCBB6DC" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<taxonomicName id="E967E7EA6DD3EF35A4C188840E26509F" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Solanum multiflorum" order="Solanales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="multiflorum">
<emphasis id="7E266F1B51FB13D325349C4C676271BE" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Solanum multiflorum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was treated as a variety of &quot; 
<taxonomicName id="561B344CC0B9C64F029C4E348D118676" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Solanum indicum" order="Solanales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="indicum">
<emphasis id="F45D0B1E7524C276B1B87D93FA09AAE9" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Solanum indicum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
&quot; (now a suppressed name, see Suppressed Names) in various Indian floras, in part due to issues with the application of 
<normalizedToken id="CA3B3093C72C146E4E80CD2A8A199407" originalValue="Roth’s">Roth's</normalizedToken>
name. It is morphologically similar and related to 
<taxonomicName id="BA7F7BC5FB13589F31F69C07034940EC" family="Solanaceae" genus="S." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="S. violaceum" order="Solanales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="violaceum">
<emphasis id="E458DD555AB8D2F9BC7B453384E17BBD" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">S. violaceum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(the name now used for the suppressed 
<taxonomicName id="A3EAB9181D174F4FE27970CD49C7F7FB" family="Solanaceae" genus="S." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="S. indicum" order="Solanales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="indicum">
<emphasis id="B40D85C44577CDEDAD1B3792F7314FD4" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">S. indicum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), both taxa are members of 
<taxonomicName id="81B24FDD619A086A848C788A0A9AA680" family="Solanaceae" genus="S." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="S. violaceum" order="Solanales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="violaceum">
<emphasis id="4BFEF0CFEA21B7FD5B93270A699BE8D5" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">S. violaceum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group of 
<bibRefCitation id="EEF14D662EC7007469945B404801731A" DOI="https://doi.org/10.1111/boj.12412" author="Aubriot, X" journalOrPublisher="Botanical Journal of the Linnean Society" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="199 - 223" refId="B8" refString="Aubriot, X, Singh, P, Knapp, S, 2016a. Tropical Asian species show the Old World clade of &quot;spiny solanums&quot; (subgenus Leptostemonum pro parte: Solanaceae) is not monophyletic. Botanical Journal of the Linnean Society 181 (2): 199 - 223, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1111/boj.12412" title="Tropical Asian species show the Old World clade of &quot; spiny solanums &quot; (subgenus Leptostemonum pro parte: Solanaceae) is not monophyletic." url="https://doi.org/10.1111/boj.12412" volume="181" year="2016 a">Aubriot et al. (2016a)</bibRefCitation>
, along with 
<taxonomicName id="EDA8BBA56D933517A758554979318F6E" family="Solanaceae" genus="S." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="S. hovei" order="Solanales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="hovei">
<emphasis id="FA2AD6F0DC9813A6B3E8CC057E181117" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">S. hovei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="AD731BA304A0A4226B4AEEA2EDA0D7DA" family="Solanaceae" genus="S." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="S. deflexicarpum" order="Solanales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="deflexicarpum">
<emphasis id="449903E326C43823F735E15E05042603" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">S. deflexicarpum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName id="B9AE42EE8FED7F74A7958EDAF3FDABF1" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Solanum multiflorum" order="Solanales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="multiflorum">
<emphasis id="08343770960A832B54A42D9B1FBBF60B" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Solanum multiflorum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is sympatric with 
<taxonomicName id="CD1435A71934D0B67BB8B628F5555DE7" family="Solanaceae" genus="S." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="S. violaceum" order="Solanales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="violaceum">
<emphasis id="401B2AEB831FDFF73B86F73E425BC660" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">S. violaceum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and can be distinguished from it in its usually branched inflorescences with congested pedicels, long, soft pubescence and its short fruiting pedicels that are strongly deflexed rather than widely spreading. The leaves of 
<taxonomicName id="814FF2C4B52C28D9DAE0B558557148DA" family="Solanaceae" genus="S." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="S. multiflorum" order="Solanales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="multiflorum">
<emphasis id="A44E3EB51C0AB87042EAD9D505EDBB7C" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">S. multiflorum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are usually more deeply lobed than those of 
<taxonomicName id="C2279FBA0A4E8019B8BBA2A45C426EF4" family="Solanaceae" genus="S." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="S. violaceum" order="Solanales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="violaceum">
<emphasis id="17ADE9AD43A91EF13D337A8C36919D04" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">S. violaceum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but 
<taxonomicName id="65C5753504A63EFCAB5A1F811C4FD08F" family="Solanaceae" genus="S." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="S. violaceum" order="Solanales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="violaceum">
<emphasis id="9AEBC9A3FE44010920B6EDC13EA932AE" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">S. violaceum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is extremely variable and this does not always hold. 
<taxonomicName id="69E9ECC63696F05A82016F76D619FC54" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Solanum multiflorum" order="Solanales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="multiflorum">
<emphasis id="448FD4C7EB0EE33B45524D936EFFBA1E" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Solanum multiflorum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
shares the strongly deflexed fruiting pedicels with 
<taxonomicName id="5623AF9866A61C59510C5FE758895860" family="Solanaceae" genus="S." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="S. deflexicarpum" order="Solanales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="deflexicarpum">
<emphasis id="BDEB2C204AB4A5C477080175A3F3F5CB" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">S. deflexicarpum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
of China but differs from that species in its more copious pubescence, more deeply lobed leaves and usually purple (rather than white) flowers.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="C5120EFA12E8D25B5D9936C3C7A054DF" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
The species names proposed by Albrecht Wilhelm Roth were published in 1819 by 
<bibRefCitation id="430EC620CA4BCC7272BF80EEDE58A465" author="Roemer, JJ" journalOrPublisher="Sida" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" refId="B208" refString="Roemer, JJ, Schultes, JA, 1819. Systema vegetabilium, 15th edn. [bis]. Vol. 4. J.G. Cotta, Stuttgart." title="Systema vegetabilium, 15 th edn. [bis]. Vol. 4. J. G. Cotta, Stuttgart." year="1819">Roemer and Schultes (1819)</bibRefCitation>
, two years before they were published by Roth himself (
<bibRefCitation id="401453F116CA3A6662329486E19B0EAC" DOI="https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.title.10723" author="Roth, AW" journalOrPublisher="Sida" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" refId="B209" refString="Roth, AW, 1821. Novae plantarum species praesetim Indiae orientalis ex collections Doct. Benj. Heynii. H. Vogler, Halberstadt. https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.title.10723" title="Novae plantarum species praesetim Indiae orientalis ex collections Doct. Benj. Heynii. H. Vogler, Halberstadt." url="https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.title.10723" year="1821">Roth 1821</bibRefCitation>
). Descriptions in 
<bibRefCitation id="56706FF2228D1687C07726804B18CABD" author="Roemer, JJ" journalOrPublisher="Sida" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" refId="B208" refString="Roemer, JJ, Schultes, JA, 1819. Systema vegetabilium, 15th edn. [bis]. Vol. 4. J.G. Cotta, Stuttgart." title="Systema vegetabilium, 15 th edn. [bis]. Vol. 4. J. G. Cotta, Stuttgart." year="1819">Roemer and Schultes (1819)</bibRefCitation>
are abbreviated from 
<normalizedToken id="CD5E26FC053BC9297BE7EE949A9845C1" originalValue="Roth’s">Roth's</normalizedToken>
longer ones published in 1821; no new material was apparently seen (see 
<bibRefCitation id="33DA6F598EE6F2F1B91E0A50B10DB41D" DOI="https://doi.org/10.1002/tax.12449" author="Turner, IM" journalOrPublisher="Taxon" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="365 - 428" refId="B249" refString="Turner, IM, 2021. Heyne, Roth, Roemer and Schultes, and the plant names published in Novae plantarum species praesertim Indiae orientalis. Taxon 70 (2): 365 - 428, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1002/tax.12449" title="Heyne, Roth, Roemer and Schultes, and the plant names published in Novae plantarum species praesertim Indiae orientalis." url="https://doi.org/10.1002/tax.12449" volume="70" year="2021">Turner 2021</bibRefCitation>
). Material at Edinburgh from Robert 
<normalizedToken id="6D681DD0EED4BA514E03A909034FBA07" originalValue="Wight’s">Wight's</normalizedToken>
personal herbarium (here as probable isoneotypes) is in better condition than the sheet (K000759413) in the Wallich hebarium designated as the neotype. The numbering of 
<normalizedToken id="0C5270C3B06F3A28404D13CDC5E151D8" originalValue="Wight’s">Wight's</normalizedToken>
herbarium was done after the fact specimens bearing the same number may or may not be duplicates of the neotype.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="068C88D16DB03872FD282F29E87A34CA" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<taxonomicName id="890B37C472995199A333FAA444DBED49" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Solanum himalense subsp. var. var. soumbe" order="Solanales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="himalense" subSpecies="var." variety="soumbe">Solanum himalense var. soumbe</taxonomicName>
was described based on the collection 
<emphasis id="BA6CF2F982F78E1E60C6B35C0F580A3F" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Leschenault de la Tour 163</emphasis>
seen by 
<bibRefCitation id="0734CFFC1932809C87BB7D3A97C1BE50" author="Dunal, M-F" journalOrPublisher=") Prodromus systematis naturalis regni vegetabilis" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="1 - 690" refId="B73" refString="Dunal, M-F, 1852. Solanaceae. In: Candolle AP de (Ed.) Prodromus systematis naturalis regni vegetabilis 13 (1): 1 - 690" title="Solanaceae. In: Candolle AP de (Ed." volume="13" year="1852">Dunal (1852)</bibRefCitation>
in Paris. From the three specimens with this number at P we have selected the specimen (P00055586) with an annotation in 
<normalizedToken id="40964827AE5B95E633D0E39171FF48BD" originalValue="Dunal’s">Dunal's</normalizedToken>
hand as the lectotype.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="277CEF917FBF3812454B9637F629CDB3" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
The collection 
<emphasis id="C0E30A7A9D2FC9859E12E558825CCF52" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Hohenacker 1074</emphasis>
was cited from two herbaria (&quot;hb. Van Heurck et hb. DC&quot;) in the protologue of 
<taxonomicName id="2EF337E5C4968D93BC2627B9D2156CA9" family="Solanaceae" genus="S." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="S. erosum" order="Solanales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="erosum">
<emphasis id="22A408AFFFDB63019BF7C61D345EB662" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">S. erosum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Van Heurck 1870). The Van Heurck herbarium, previously held in Antwerp at AWH, has now been acquired by BR, but sheets are still barcoded with the AWH herbarium code. We have selected the duplicate of 
<emphasis id="2598C784B8B15026FAB132709D9391F0" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Hohenacker 1074</emphasis>
held in BR (AWH10071571) as the lectotype for 
<taxonomicName id="DD0220953F843D87CEB95894B487B2A8" family="Solanaceae" genus="S." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="S. erosum" order="Solanales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="erosum">
<emphasis id="F5A17C7E7A03BAD03460B0E19599D2B5" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">S. erosum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; this collection is widely distributed.
</paragraph>
